rom hospitals, funerals, and cemeteries to autopsies and death registrations. As they did so, imperial consulates pushed against the workings of both the Egyptian state and each other, expanding their governments' material and performative power. Ultimately, this book reveals how European imperial powers did not so much claim Alexandria as their own, as they maneuvered, manipulated, and cajoled their empires into Egypt.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAlienszEgyptzAlexandriaxDeathxHistory. 0aDeathxPolitical aspectszEgyptzAlexandriaxHistory. 0aVisitors, ForeignzEgyptzAlexandriaxDeathxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Egypt (see also Ancient / Egypt).2bisacsh  aAlexandria.  aBritish Empire.  aDeath Studies.  aDeath.  aEgypt.  aFrench Empire.  abelonging.  acolonialism and imperialism.  aconsulates.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503610507zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503610507423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503610507.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020